# Arm Control

## Joint Layout (per arm, coaxial)
1. **Shoulder pitch** — RS03 sits inside the torso, output face points outward left/right
2. **Shoulder roll** — RS03 in PETG shoulder housing, bolted to pitch output
3. **Upper arm yaw** — RS03 inline with upper arm tube
4. **Elbow pitch** — RS03 at the elbow joint

Shoulder housing has integrated L-bracket tabs that bolt to the torso 2020 extrusions via M5 + sliding T-nuts.

## Multi-Motor Bus Sharing
All arm motors on one arm share a single CAN bus and single `RobStrideBus` instance. The `Arm` class creates one bus and passes it to each `Motor`. Each motor has a unique CAN ID.

## Motion Safety
- Always enforce joint limits from `config/robot.yaml` before sending commands
- Speed limits should be conservative during development (< 10 rad/s)
- Torque limits should stay well below peak (< 30 N·m) until mechanical structure is proven
- Every motion script must disable all motors in a finally/cleanup block
